    "executiveSummary": {
      "text": "AerCap is the largest listed aircraft lessor and its investment case is driven by fleet quality, lease yields, funding access and residual value discipline. The company benefits when airlines want capacity but prefer not to own aircraft outright, especially in a market where manufacturer delivery delays keep equipment tight. The question is less about top-line growth than about how long the current favourable supply-demand balance can support lease economics without a credit or travel downturn intervening."
